# Cursor Lifecycle Adapters

Use this file as the compatibility layer between Cursor and Claude Code lifecycle semantics.
Do not rewrite `ia/skills/*/SKILL.md`; adapt execution strategy here.

## stage-file-plan

- caller_agent: `stage-file` (when invoking gated mutation tools).
- pair seam: planner-only. Produce tuples and stop.
- handoff artifact: write tuples in target `ia/projects/*master-plan*.md` section expected by apply step.
- recommended model: Max/Opus preferred.
- caveat: Cursor has no forced model handoff; ask for explicit user confirmation before apply.

## stage-file-apply

- caller_agent: `stage-file`.
- reserve-id: yes, before new ids run `bash tools/scripts/reserve-id.sh TECH <count>` (or FEAT/BUG/ART/AUDIO).
- pair seam: consumes planner tuples only; do not re-plan.
- recommended model: Sonnet/Composer2 acceptable.
- caveat: never hand-edit `ia/state/id-counter.json`.

## project-new

- caller_agent: `project-new` for `backlog_record_upsert`.
- reserve-id: yes, use `reserve-id.sh`.
- pair seam: planner pass (summary + payload) then apply pass.
- recommended model: Max/Opus preferred for planning clarity.

## project-new-apply

- caller_agent: `project-new`.
- reserve-id: yes.
- recommended model: Sonnet/Composer2 acceptable.
- caveat: create exactly one issue/spec pair and stop.

## plan-review

- pair seam: review verdict + fix tuples only.
- recommended model: Max/Opus preferred.
- caveat: classify findings by severity before any changes.

## plan-fix-apply

- pair seam: apply tuples only.
- recommended model: Sonnet/Composer2 acceptable.
- caveat: no scope creep beyond fix tuples.

## opus-code-review

- pair seam: review output only (`PASS` / `minor` / `critical`) and optional fix tuples.
- recommended model: Max/Opus preferred.
- caveat: keep evidence anchored to spec + invariants.

## code-fix-apply

- pair seam: apply only tuple set from review.
- recommended model: Sonnet/Composer2 acceptable.
- caveat: after apply, rerun verification sequence.

## stage-closeout-plan

- caller_agent: `closeout`.
- pair seam: planner emits one stage-scoped closeout tuple batch.
- recommended model: Max/Opus preferred.
- caveat: include explicit destructive-op confirmation checkpoint before delete/archive actions.

## stage-closeout-apply

- caller_agent: `closeout` (for `backlog_record_upsert`, glossary/rule/spec mutation tools when needed).
- reserve-id: no.
- recommended model: Sonnet/Composer2 acceptable.
- caveat: run non-destructive migrations first, destructive ops only after confirmation.

## plan-author

- mode: bulk Stage 1xN authoring (single pass across all tasks in stage).
- recommended model: Max/Opus strongly preferred.
- caveat: if model budget insufficient, split by phase and keep one pass per phase.

## opus-audit

- mode: bulk Stage 1xN synthesis of `§Audit`.
- recommended model: Max/Opus strongly preferred.
- caveat: if context becomes large, run per task and merge at stage end.

## master-plan-new

- caller_agent: `master-plan-new` when invoking `glossary_row_create` / `rule_create`.
- reserve-id: optional, only if skill route creates issue records (normally no).
- recommended model: Max/Opus preferred.
- caveat: output must be fully decomposed steps (no skeleton placeholders).

## ship-stage

- caller_agent: `ship-stage` for mutation calls.
- chain strategy: execute in fixed order `author -> implement -> verify-loop -> code-review -> audit -> closeout`.
- checkpoint rule: stop after each sub-skill and summarize status before continuing.
- recommended model: Max/Opus for planner/review steps; Sonnet/Composer2 acceptable for apply steps.
- caveat: for long stages, split by task and open fresh session between tasks.

## release-rollout

- caller_agent: `release-rollout` (and `release-rollout-track` for tracker flips).
- chain strategy: one rollout row per session by default.
- checkpoint rule: after each column flip, persist ticket and stop if unresolved dependency appears.
- recommended model: Max/Opus preferred.

## release-rollout-track

- caller_agent: `release-rollout-track`.
- recommended model: Sonnet/Composer2 acceptable.
- caveat: mechanical update only; no scope decisions.

## skill-train

- mode: retrospective only, never auto-apply patches.
- recommended model: Max/Opus preferred.
- caveat: write proposal artifact, require explicit human approval before any skill changes.
